The Solution
We introduced a flexible rate engine that enables:
1. Tier-Based Time Brackets
Example:
0–8 hours
8–10 hours
10–12 hours
12+ hours
2. Cost vs. Price Separation
Cost rates → What you pay crew
Price rates → What you charge customers
3. Automation on Time Changes
When schedules are modified:
Overtime logic recalculates automatically
Cost updates propagate without manual edits
Reduced need for spreadsheet corrections
This directly addressed the behavioral pattern we saw in the data.
4. Bulk Rate Assignment
Assign rate structures to multiple crew members instantly.
5. Licensing Strategy
Launched under:
Crew Scheduling Pro
Quoting & Invoicing add-on
Supporting migration to our new licensing model.

